<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>Which is an example of an automatic stabilizer during a recession?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Congress passing a new stimulus package</option>
            <option letter="b">The Fed lowering interest rates</option>
            <option letter="c">Progressive income tax collecting less revenue</option>
            <option letter="d">The President proposing new spending programs</option>
        </options>
        <answer>c</answer>
        <explanation>Progressive income tax acts as an automatic stabilizer because during a recession, as incomes fall, people automatically pay less in taxes due to the progressive tax structure. This happens without requiring any new legislation, helping to maintain disposable income and consumer spending.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
